## 4. Routing Model

Three route groups under `app/`:

| Group       | Auth requirement                                          | Purpose                                     |
| ----------- | --------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------- |
| `index.tsx` | none                                                      | Bootstrap landing → redirect by auth status |
| `(auth)/`   | public (no guard)                                         | Onboarding, login, register, password reset |
| `(app)/`    | guarded — `<Redirect href="/(auth)/login" />` if unauth   | Authenticated experience                    |

**Root `_layout.tsx` provider order (top-down):**

```
QueryClientProvider
  └── AuthProvider
       └── ThemeProvider
            └── SplashGate           // blocks render until AuthProvider.bootstrapped
                 └── <Stack>
                      ├── <Stack.Screen name="index" />
                      ├── <Stack.Screen name="(auth)" />
                      └── <Stack.Screen name="(app)" />
```

`SplashGate` calls `SplashScreen.hideAsync()` only after `bootstrapped === true`, so the splash stays up while SecureStore is read.

