## 9. Theming and Brand

### 9.1 Palette (`constants/manda-theme.ts`)

`MANDA` exports brand greens (`green`, `greenDeep`, `greenInk`, `greenSoft`, `greenMint`, `greenBright`), neutrals (`white`, `paper`, `cardBorder`, `divider`, `ink`, `inkMuted`, `inkSubtle`), status (`warn`, `warnSoft`, `danger`, `dangerSoft`), and bubble colors (`bubbleMe`, `bubbleMeInk`, `bubbleThem`, `bubbleThemInk`). Use these for brand surfaces.

`MANDA_FONT` maps semantic weights to font family names: `regular | medium | semiBold | bold | extraBold`.

### 9.2 Legacy theme (`constants/theme.ts`)

`Colors.light / Colors.dark` + platform-aware `Fonts` exist for `themed-text` / `themed-view`. Prefer `MANDA` for new components; keep `Colors` only where existing primitives already depend on it.

### 9.3 Canonical primitives

`components/manda/*` is the canonical library: `Screen`, `PrimaryButton`, `TextField`, `OtpBoxes`, `Avatar`, `MandaGlyph`, `MandaWordmark`. **Reach for these before introducing new primitives.**

---

## 10. Conventions

- **File naming:** kebab-case for files (`auth-provider.tsx`, `manda-theme.ts`); route group folders in `(parens)`.
- **Imports:** prefer `@/...` over deep relative paths.
- **Strict TypeScript:** fix type errors at the source, don't `as any`.
- **No business logic in route files** — keep `app/*.tsx` thin; push logic into `providers/`, `lib/`, hooks.
- **All HTTP via `lib/api/*`** — never raw `fetch`/`axios` in components.
- **Error display:** show `ApiError.message` directly (Portuguese from API).
- **React Compiler is on** — don't pre-emptively wrap with `useMemo` / `useCallback`. Add them only when profiling shows a measured regression.
- **Cleartext HTTP** is allowed on Android in dev (`usesCleartextTraffic: true` in `app.json`). Production uses HTTPS via Cloudflare Tunnel.

